# README #


### What is this repository for? ###

* Segfault is a unix software that aims to extract text form an image.
* v0.1

### How do I get thing up? ###


```
#!sh

make

```

### Training the neural network

You need to download the training data at https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/54394996/data.zip and unzip it in a `data` directory a the root of the project.

The name of each directory corresponds to the code of the character within. Characters have been rendered with 122 different fonts, at 3 different rotation angles (-5°, 0°, 5°).

Then, go to `src/train`, `make train` and call `./train` to see the list of available commands.

